    "<p>Architectural historian and architect.": [],
    "Richardson was the son of Albert Edmund Richardson, a printer, and Mary Ann Richardson (maiden name, unrelated).": [],
    "After attending the Boys British School, Highgate (north London), he was apprenticed in 1895 to the architect/engineer Thomas Page (1803-1877), joining the offices of Evelyn Hellicar (1898-1902), Leonard Stokes (1902-3), and Frank T. Verity (1903-6).": [
